step 1: create a github repository.
step 2: create a virtual env and activate it.(python3 -m venv ENV_NAME and source ENV_NAME/bin/activate)
step 3: clone the repoository. (first confirm whether git is initialised or not, if yes: git clone URL)
step 4: install necessary Packages for the project. (pip install django,flask,pytest,etc)
step 5: store all needed Packages into a reqirements.txt file (pip freeze > requirements.txt) 

NOTE: to install Packages from an existing requirements.txt file, (pip install -r requirements.txt)

